      • withRollupLimit

        public ExBestOffersOverrides.Builder withRollupLimit(int rollupLimit)
        Use this function to set rollupLimit
        Parameters:
        rollupLimit - The volume limit to use when rolling up returned sizes. The exact definition of the limit depends on the rollupModel. If no limit is provided it will use minimum stake as default the value. Ignored if no rollup model is specified.
        Returns:
        Builder

      • withRollupLiabilityThreshold

        public ExBestOffersOverrides.Builder withRollupLiabilityThreshold(double rollupLiabilityThreshold)
        Use this function to set rollupLiabilityThreshold
        Parameters:
        rollupLiabilityThreshold - Only applicable when rollupModel is MANAGED_LIABILITY. The rollup model switches from being stake based to liability based at the smallest lay price which is >= rollupLiabilityThreshold.service level default (TBD). Not supported as yet.
        Returns:
        Builder

      • withRollupLiabilityFactor

        public ExBestOffersOverrides.Builder withRollupLiabilityFactor(int rollupLiabilityFactor)
        Use this function to set rollupLiabilityFactor
        Parameters:
        rollupLiabilityFactor - Only applicable when rollupModel is MANAGED_LIABILITY. (rollupLiabilityFactor * rollupLimit) is the minimum liabilty the user is deemed to be comfortable with. After the rollupLiabilityThreshold price subsequent volumes will be rolled up to minimum value such that the liability >= the minimum liability.service level default (5). Not supported as yet.
        Returns:
        Builder
